But, Norman, she has never
worked in her life before.

02:52.131 --> 02:53.549
I thought you'd be
sympathetic.

02:53.632 --> 02:55.050
I am sympathetic, but, please,

02:55.134 --> 02:57.052
why do I have to train her?

02:57.136 --> 02:59.180
Let her work in
someone else's section.

02:59.263 --> 03:01.140
She's willing
and needs the job.

03:01.223 --> 03:02.683
She's recently divorced.

03:02.766 --> 03:04.685
I'm a widow with four kids.

03:04.768 --> 03:06.187
Jerry should never
have died.

03:06.270 --> 03:10.232
I'd be better off.
I could've divorced him.

03:10.316 --> 03:11.984
Is that her?

03:12.067 --> 03:13.194
Yes.

03:13.277 --> 03:16.739
We're going to need
a special locker for the hat.

03:19.325 --> 03:20.409
This way.

03:20.492 --> 03:23.412
This is
quite a day for me.
I'll bet it is.

03:23.495 --> 03:26.707
I was so excited,
I left an hour early
so I wouldn't be late.

03:26.790 --> 03:31.921
It took 45 minutes
to find parking.

03:32.004 --> 03:34.048
We park inside the building.

03:34.131 --> 03:36.842
I just moved
to an apartment
near the airport.

03:36.926 --> 03:38.010
Ah.

03:38.093 --> 03:39.511
Hey, Violet,
what it is?

03:39.595 --> 03:40.679
Hi, Eddie.

03:40.763 --> 03:42.223
What do you hear
about your promotion?

03:42.306 --> 03:44.225
Nothing now.
Uh, Eddie Smith...

03:44.308 --> 03:45.684
Judy Bernly.

03:45.768 --> 03:47.186
Judy starts work today.

03:47.269 --> 03:48.479
What?

03:48.562 --> 03:52.483
How will I ever
get out of this
mail room prison

03:52.566 --> 03:54.485
if they keep hiring
from outside?

03:54.568 --> 03:56.987
Lady, you're going
to hate it here.

03:58.697 --> 03:59.740
Judy.

03:59.823 --> 04:02.243
Okay. Now, we're
on the 12th floor.

04:02.326 --> 04:04.245
Above us is
the executive suite,

04:04.328 --> 04:08.249
where the president,
Mr. Hinkle, is
and the chairman of the board.

04:08.332 --> 04:09.250
It sounds so big.

04:09.333 --> 04:11.252
It is.
I've been here 12 years.

04:11.335 --> 04:13.254
I've never even seen
the chairman of the board.

04:13.337 --> 04:17.257
12 years? All I've done
is be a housewife.

04:17.341 --> 04:19.760
I wanted to ask you
about my salary.

04:19.843 --> 04:22.263
That's a very
touchy subject
around here.

04:22.346 --> 04:24.265
You'll have
to take that up

04:24.348 --> 04:25.766
with our boss
Mr. Hart.

04:25.849 --> 04:28.269
Oh, I'm sorry.
It's all so new.

04:28.352 --> 04:30.271
You'll get
the hang of it.

04:30.354 --> 04:32.273
Then you'll really
be sorry.

04:33.357 --> 04:34.441
Come on.

04:37.361 --> 04:40.447
Well, welcome
to the front lines.

04:45.869 --> 04:48.789
Uh-oh. Here comes
General Patton.

04:48.872 --> 04:50.291
Violet, just a moment.

04:50.374 --> 04:51.458
Come on.

04:51.542 --> 04:52.960
Uh, just a moment.

04:53.043 --> 04:54.128
Violet?

04:54.211 --> 04:55.879
Oh, yes, Roz.
So sorry.

04:55.963 --> 05:00.301
I've been meaning to talk to you
about Mr. Hart's rules
on office decor.

05:00.384 --> 05:02.469
They seem to be getting
lax in your section.

05:02.553 --> 05:04.722
Really? How?

05:04.805 --> 05:06.223
I've typed it up here.

05:06.307 --> 05:08.225
"No coffee cups
on the desks.

05:08.309 --> 05:10.227
"No personal items
left in view‒

05:10.311 --> 05:11.395
"photos...

05:11.478 --> 05:12.896
plants, et cetera."

05:12.980 --> 05:16.066
We mustn't look
cluttered or sloppy.
Mm-mmm.

05:16.150 --> 05:17.151
An office that...

05:17.234 --> 05:19.528
looks efficient
is efficient,
looks efficient
is efficient,

05:19.611 --> 05:21.488
as Mr. Hart says.
As Mr. Hart says.

05:21.572 --> 05:22.323
Oh, hello.

05:22.406 --> 05:26.535
Judy Bernly, Roz Keith,
Mr. Hart's administrative
assistant.

05:26.618 --> 05:28.746
Judy is starting
today.

05:28.829 --> 05:30.247
It's nice to meet you.

05:30.331 --> 05:33.250
Welcome to Consolidated.
I hope you enjoy it.

05:33.334 --> 05:34.752
We're all
a happy bunch.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.253
I think so.

05:36.337 --> 05:38.255
Put this
on the bulletin board.

05:38.339 --> 05:40.758
I know just where
to stick it.

05:40.841 --> 05:44.345
Judy, if there's
anything I can do
to help you settle in,

05:44.428 --> 05:47.931
just drop on by.
Thank you.

05:51.727 --> 05:53.270
One thing you should know
about dear Roz‒

05:53.354 --> 05:55.564
she's the eyes, ears, nose,
and throat of Mr. Hart.

05:55.647 --> 05:59.777
Anything she hears,
he hears.
She's a company spy?

05:59.860 --> 06:01.278
Shh! I wouldn't say that.

06:01.362 --> 06:03.697
If you gossip
in the ladies' room,

06:03.781 --> 06:06.200
check under the stalls
for her shoes.

06:06.283 --> 06:07.701
Happy birthday, Myra.

06:07.785 --> 06:09.703
She and Roz
are like this.

06:09.787 --> 06:11.705
This section's
divided into three zones,

06:11.789 --> 06:13.207
each with a supervisor.

06:13.290 --> 06:16.210
As senior,
the other two supervisors
report to me.

06:16.293 --> 06:20.339
I report to Mr. Hart.
That's his office there.
He was just made vice president.

06:20.422 --> 06:24.051
I've never seen anyone
leapfrog so fast.

06:24.134 --> 06:26.929
I have the bad back
to prove it.

06:27.012 --> 06:29.515
Margaret, anything serious?

06:29.598 --> 06:31.058
Nothing so far.

06:31.141 --> 06:32.226
Uh-huh.

06:32.309 --> 06:34.728
Margaret, please.
Roz is on my case.

06:34.812 --> 06:35.938
Sorry.

06:36.021 --> 06:39.400
I remember
when he was just
a management trainee.

06:39.483 --> 06:42.403
In fact, I'm the one
who trained him.

06:42.486 --> 06:44.738
What's he like?

06:47.825 --> 06:49.785
I like to think, Judy,

06:49.868 --> 06:51.787
if there is a word

06:51.870 --> 06:54.331
to describe my philosophy
of business...

06:55.499 --> 06:57.709
it's "teamwork."

06:57.793 --> 07:01.463
Everybody
working together.

07:01.547 --> 07:04.675
You girls, of course,
never got a chance
to play football

07:04.758 --> 07:06.218
or baseball.

07:07.010 --> 07:09.221
And I've always felt
like that's unfortunate

07:09.304 --> 07:12.724
because I think it's‒
it's probably
the best place

07:12.808 --> 07:15.769
to learn what teamwork
is all about.

07:15.853 --> 07:18.689
I remember Coach Frye
used to tell us

07:18.772 --> 07:22.818
"a chain is only as strong
as its weakest link."

07:25.320 --> 07:28.699
Its weakest link‒
God damn it!

07:29.825 --> 07:31.076
Get this chair fixed.

07:31.160 --> 07:36.582
Well, I...
I'm not going to bore you
with a long harangue.

07:36.665 --> 07:39.585
Just suffice to say that
it's a jungle out there,

07:39.668 --> 07:41.086
but if we work together,

07:41.170 --> 07:43.464
we'll cut the balls off
the competition

07:43.547 --> 07:46.800
and be sitting pretty
on top of the hill.

07:51.346 --> 07:52.806
Thank you, sir.

07:52.890 --> 07:54.558
I'm happy
to be working here.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.059
Well, you're
a welcome addition,

07:56.143 --> 07:59.021
and a damn pretty one, too,
if I might add.

07:59.104 --> 08:00.397
Thank you, sir.
I mean that.

08:00.481 --> 08:03.317
You should see the crones
coming through here lately.

08:03.400 --> 08:04.943
Real pathetic.
Right, Violet?

08:06.278 --> 08:08.614
Oh, Violet,
my wife's coming by later.

08:08.697 --> 08:10.616
I'd like to get her
a present.

08:10.699 --> 08:12.493
Could you pick out a scarf?

08:12.576 --> 08:14.036
We've discussed
this before.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.663
It's not my place
to shop‒

08:16.747 --> 08:18.665
God damn it.
For five minutes

08:18.749 --> 08:20.167
I've been talking
about teamwork.

08:20.250 --> 08:22.336
You're not there
for the hand-off.

08:22.419 --> 08:23.879
All I'm saying,
Mr. Hart,

08:23.962 --> 08:25.881
is my job description
says nothing

08:25.964 --> 08:28.300
about making
purchases
for your wife.

08:28.383 --> 08:31.303
All I'm saying is
I like people around me

08:31.386 --> 08:33.304
who are flexible
and get along.

08:33.388 --> 08:34.806
When I ask an employee,

08:34.890 --> 08:37.433
especially one who wants
to be promoted to management,

08:37.518 --> 08:38.936
I expect
a little cooperation.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.102
You savvy?

08:40.187 --> 08:41.270
Savvy.

08:41.355 --> 08:43.774
Good. Silk, blue,
maybe a red stripe.

08:43.857 --> 08:46.276
You're talking
to the right person.

08:46.360 --> 08:47.778
Violet's the best.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.279
First person I met here.

08:49.363 --> 08:51.281
Knows more about
what's going on

08:51.365 --> 08:53.450
than anybody
but Mr. Hinkle.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.369
Oh, a deer.

08:55.452 --> 08:56.912
Yeah. Lucky shot.

08:56.995 --> 08:58.914
Listen, if you ever
have anything

08:58.997 --> 09:01.416
of a serious nature
on your mind,

09:01.500 --> 09:03.377
feel free
to talk to me,

09:03.460 --> 09:06.880
because that's actually
why I have my office
on this floor‒

09:06.964 --> 09:09.383
to be close to my girls.
Okay?

09:09.466 --> 09:10.884
Certainly. Thank you.

09:10.968 --> 09:11.969
Good.

09:12.970 --> 09:15.180
Oh, is Doralee
back yet?

09:17.140 --> 09:18.517
No.

09:18.600 --> 09:20.018
Get me coffee
then, Violet.

09:20.102 --> 09:22.396
No sugar.
Just Skinny and Sweet.

09:22.479 --> 09:23.647
Yes, sir.

09:28.318 --> 09:31.947
Well, that's
Franklin Hart, Jr.

09:32.030 --> 09:35.033
But to me
he'll always be
F. Hart.

09:36.827 --> 09:38.412
Oh, good.

09:38.495 --> 09:39.663
She's back.

09:41.331 --> 09:43.125
Hi, Violet.
How's everything going?

09:43.208 --> 09:44.793
Oh, Doralee,
your boss wants coffee.

09:44.876 --> 09:48.297
Great. I just got back
from gassing up his car.

09:48.380 --> 09:50.340
I'm filling one tank
or another.

09:50.424 --> 09:51.842
This is Judy Bernly.

09:51.925 --> 09:54.344
Judy will be working
in my section.

09:54.428 --> 09:55.846
Doralee Rhodes.

09:55.929 --> 09:57.347
Nice to meet you.

09:57.431 --> 09:59.266
Hope everybody's been
treating you friendly

09:59.349 --> 10:00.809
and showing you around.

10:00.892 --> 10:02.811
Everybody's been
very nice, thank you.

10:02.894 --> 10:05.814
If there's anything
I can do, just holler.

10:05.897 --> 10:08.442
I know what it's like
to be the new girl.

10:08.525 --> 10:10.110
Thank you.

10:12.362 --> 10:14.781
Judy, over here.

10:14.865 --> 10:17.784
This is your typewriter,
Dictaphone, adding machine.

10:17.868 --> 10:20.704
I better get you
a locker for that hat.

10:36.511 --> 10:37.596
Hello.

10:37.679 --> 10:39.222
Hello.

10:40.724 --> 10:41.808
Uh...

10:41.892 --> 10:42.809
yes.

10:44.061 --> 10:45.187
Hello?

10:51.735 --> 10:54.529
Jo's leaving.
They won't let her
work part-time.

10:54.613 --> 10:57.991
Of course they won't.
It would make things
too convenient.

10:58.075 --> 11:00.827
Hi, Violet. Hi, Judy.
How's it going?

11:00.911 --> 11:02.245
Fine, thank you.

11:02.329 --> 11:04.748
Violet's going to show me
around outside.

11:04.831 --> 11:07.751
Hart's asked me
to buy his wife a scarf.

11:07.834 --> 11:10.420
Why doesn't he ask
Doralee?

11:10.504 --> 11:12.923
She does
everything else for him.

11:13.006 --> 11:14.424
Oh, she's too tired.

11:14.508 --> 11:17.678
They've been
in conference together
all morning.

11:17.761 --> 11:19.179
We'll see you later.

11:19.262 --> 11:20.681
Come on, Judy.

11:20.764 --> 11:21.848
Have fun.

11:21.932 --> 11:24.017
Your salmon
looks good. Mmm!

11:24.101 --> 11:25.185
$20?

11:25.268 --> 11:26.687
I like this.

11:26.770 --> 11:29.690
What did Margaret mean
about Doralee?

11:29.773 --> 11:32.693
Well, rumor has it
that, uh...

11:32.776 --> 11:34.695
she is banging the boss.

11:34.778 --> 11:37.781
She and Mr. Hart?

11:37.864 --> 11:39.282
I think that's awful.

11:39.366 --> 11:41.284
Well, live
and let live.

11:41.368 --> 11:44.287
Though, frankly,
I credit her
with more brains.

11:44.371 --> 11:45.789
Certainly more taste.

11:45.872 --> 11:47.290
That's how
my husband left.

11:47.374 --> 11:50.293
He was having an affair
with his secretary.

11:50.377 --> 11:53.296
I don't think Hart
will leave his wife.

11:53.380 --> 11:55.799
She's been
too good a meal ticket
all these years.

11:55.882 --> 11:58.927
Besides, she's bananas.
She adores him.

12:05.642 --> 12:07.561
Doralee, would you
grab your pad

12:07.644 --> 12:10.397
and bring your pretty face
in here, please?

12:10.480 --> 12:12.149
Yes, sir.

12:23.285 --> 12:24.745
Hold it right there.

12:24.828 --> 12:26.079
What?

12:27.330 --> 12:29.249
Turn around
just a second.

12:29.332 --> 12:31.001
Something wrong?

12:32.085 --> 12:34.254
Have I got something
on my dress?

12:34.337 --> 12:35.255
Nothing's wrong.

12:35.338 --> 12:37.299
Matter of fact,
everything is...

12:37.382 --> 12:38.884
very, very right.

12:41.344 --> 12:43.555
Shall we begin,
Mr. Hart?

12:43.638 --> 12:44.723
Yeah. Um...

12:44.806 --> 12:47.851
take a letter
to Vernon Henshaw

12:47.934 --> 12:50.061
over at Metropolitan Mutual.

12:51.021 --> 12:53.106
Dear Vern,

12:53.190 --> 12:54.608
as you know,

12:54.691 --> 12:57.778
the chairman of the board
of Consolidated Companies,

12:57.861 --> 13:00.030
Mr. Russell Tinsworthy,

13:00.113 --> 13:02.783
spends most of his time
in Brazil

13:02.866 --> 13:07.204
working on the jungle
clearance operation.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.955
Consequent‒

13:09.039 --> 13:10.499
Oh, the pencils dropped.

13:10.582 --> 13:13.084
It's all right.
I'll get it.

13:14.836 --> 13:17.380
Here, let me...

13:17.464 --> 13:20.383
Let me‒
Let me help you
with those.

13:20.467 --> 13:22.886
That's okay, really.
I've got them.

13:22.969 --> 13:25.180
There you go.
Okay.

13:25.263 --> 13:28.767
Doralee.
Yes?

13:28.850 --> 13:30.894
About my conduct
in the office here
yesterday...

13:30.977 --> 13:35.065
I'm afraid I got
a little carried away. I'd...

13:35.148 --> 13:37.567
I'd just like
to apologize to you.

13:37.651 --> 13:39.069
Don't you worry
about it.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.321
I've been chased
by swifter men than you,

13:41.404 --> 13:43.365
and I ain't
been caught yet.

13:43.448 --> 13:47.077
Shall we get back
to our letter now?

13:47.160 --> 13:51.081
But could you just
come over here
for a second?

13:51.164 --> 13:53.333
I have a little
something for you.

13:53.416 --> 13:56.211
You know...

13:56.294 --> 13:57.754
ever since I made
that stupid mistake

13:57.838 --> 14:00.674
about the convention
in San Francisco, I...

14:00.757 --> 14:02.676
Oh, you didn't
make a mistake.

14:02.759 --> 14:04.177
I'll just have to make sure

14:04.261 --> 14:07.681
the next time I'm asked
to work at a convention,

14:07.764 --> 14:09.432
there's a convention
going on.

14:09.516 --> 14:13.687
Right. And nothing happened anyway,
so let's forget the whole thing.

14:13.770 --> 14:14.896
Fine.

14:14.980 --> 14:18.024
Doralee...

14:18.108 --> 14:20.235
you know, you mean
so much more to me

14:20.318 --> 14:22.529
than just a dumb secretary,

14:22.612 --> 14:24.573
so I bought this for you.

14:24.656 --> 14:26.074
I picked it out myself.

14:26.157 --> 14:27.868
Well, thank you.

14:28.827 --> 14:31.746
You didn't have
to do that.

14:31.830 --> 14:33.748
Oh, it's nice.

14:33.832 --> 14:36.334
It's very nice.

14:36.418 --> 14:38.461
It's also very nothing.

14:38.545 --> 14:39.963
Doralee, I'm a rich man.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.507
I've got a checkbook
on that desk.

14:42.591 --> 14:45.510
Say the word,
you can write
your own figure.

14:45.594 --> 14:47.012
I could do that now.

14:47.095 --> 14:49.389
I sign your name
better than you do.

14:49.472 --> 14:53.143
Doralee,
don't you understand?
I'm crazy about you.

14:53.226 --> 14:54.811
You're all I think about.

14:54.895 --> 14:57.981
I've told you before.
I'm a married woman.

14:58.064 --> 15:01.526
And I'm a married man.
That makes it perfect.

15:01.610 --> 15:02.944
Oh, Mr. Hart‒ Aah!

15:03.028 --> 15:04.446
Doralee, please!
I want you.

15:04.529 --> 15:05.947
Oh, for heaven's sake.

15:06.031 --> 15:08.241
What are you doing,
Mr. Hart?

15:08.325 --> 15:09.618
Call me Frank.

15:10.660 --> 15:11.745
Frank?

15:11.828 --> 15:12.996
Huh?

15:13.079 --> 15:15.707
What are you doing
on the floor?

15:15.790 --> 15:17.208
Nothing. I tripped.

15:17.292 --> 15:20.712
Hit my knee
on the damn
coffee table.

15:20.795 --> 15:21.880
Ow! Oh!

15:21.963 --> 15:23.381
Did you hurt yourself?

15:23.465 --> 15:24.549
No.

15:24.633 --> 15:26.551
What are you
doing down here?

15:26.635 --> 15:29.554
You know I hate it
when you come here.

15:29.638 --> 15:31.056
You know that.

15:31.139 --> 15:32.557
Don't be mad at me.

15:32.641 --> 15:34.476
I just came
from the travel agency.

15:34.559 --> 15:37.062
They have the most
wonderful cruises‒

15:37.145 --> 15:38.563
Oh, hello, Doralee.

15:38.647 --> 15:40.231
Hi, Mrs. Hart.
Well, how are you?

15:40.315 --> 15:43.360
I'm fine, and you?
What a lovely scarf.

15:43.443 --> 15:46.571
It's a present
from your husband.

15:46.655 --> 15:49.074
Oh, Frank,
that was so thoughtful.

15:49.157 --> 15:51.076
I'm just glad
he appreciates you.

15:51.159 --> 15:52.994
Put it on.

15:55.622 --> 15:58.541
Oh, it's absolutely
adorable.

15:58.625 --> 16:01.086
And you are so attractive.

16:01.169 --> 16:03.546
You're sweet.
I appreciate that.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.548
Doralee,
that'll be all for now.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.717
You can just finish
the letter later on.

16:07.801 --> 16:11.388
Bye. Oh, Frank,
let me show you
these brochures.

16:11.471 --> 16:16.059
It won't take a second.
You did promise to go.
Right.

16:16.142 --> 16:19.270
Here's a lovely one.
An Italian line.

16:19.354 --> 16:21.272
Looks just like
the <i>Love Boat.</i>

16:21.356 --> 16:22.440
It does.

16:22.524 --> 16:25.819
Four weeks of sunshine.

16:25.902 --> 16:28.405
Four weeks? Are you
out of your mind?

16:28.488 --> 16:30.115
I'm not spending
four weeks of my life

16:30.198 --> 16:32.826
drifting around
on that dago boat.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.251
Well, I'll be damned.

16:41.334 --> 16:44.587
Just look and see
who got paid off
for services rendered.

16:44.671 --> 16:46.589
That's‒That's the scarf
you bought.

16:48.258 --> 16:51.678
Aw, who cares?
I suppose
she deserves it.

16:51.761 --> 16:54.222
I'll bet you
can't wait to see
the Xerox room.

16:56.224 --> 16:59.144
Now, all these rush memos
are always done

16:59.227 --> 17:00.812
on regulation
Consolidated letterhead,

17:00.895 --> 17:04.773
so you place it in here,
8 1/2 X 11.

17:04.858 --> 17:07.694
Close the bin firmly,
turn on the power.

17:09.069 --> 17:12.365
Several people
have lost their hearing
in this room!

17:12.449 --> 17:14.409
Select the number
of copies,

17:14.492 --> 17:16.411
make this a little darker,

17:16.493 --> 17:18.121
and start the print.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.622
Here it comes.

17:19.705 --> 17:22.125
If anything goes wrong,
watch this panel.

17:22.208 --> 17:24.627
The machine tells you
what to do.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.128
I'll leave you to it.

18:13.802 --> 18:14.886
Oh!

18:39.828 --> 18:41.246
You're too much.

18:41.329 --> 18:44.457
Your wife's going off
on vacation. There'll be
no stopping you.

18:44.541 --> 18:48.837
I know. Wait till you hear
this new little
scheme I've got going.

18:50.004 --> 18:52.423
Come on in here
a minute.

18:55.468 --> 18:58.763
What the hell
is going on here?

19:01.057 --> 19:02.392
I'm sorry, Mr. Hart.

19:02.475 --> 19:03.810
It was going too fast.

19:03.893 --> 19:06.855
Why didn't you just
shut it off right here?

19:06.938 --> 19:09.274
Catch you upstairs, Frank.
Great little scheme
you got here.

19:09.357 --> 19:11.067
Right here. Right here.

19:11.151 --> 19:13.278
I'm sorry, Mr. Hart.
I thought
I could keep up.

19:13.361 --> 19:15.822
Weren't you
checked out
on this machine?

19:15.905 --> 19:18.992
Any moron could
operate this.

19:19.075 --> 19:20.535
I was.

19:20.618 --> 19:23.037
I know what to do
now, sir.

19:23.121 --> 19:24.539
I suggest
you do it,

19:24.622 --> 19:26.416
or your first day
will be your last,
understand?

19:26.499 --> 19:29.085
Yes, sir.
Clean this mess up
and get back to work.

19:29.169 --> 19:30.920
Yes, sir.

20:06.956 --> 20:08.166
Dick?

20:09.250 --> 20:10.793
Oh, Judy.

20:13.046 --> 20:14.881
What are you doing here?

20:14.964 --> 20:18.718
I just dropped by to
give you these papers.

20:21.846 --> 20:23.264
They're the last.

20:23.348 --> 20:24.766
You, uh, you sign them,

20:24.849 --> 20:27.769
and then you give them
to your lawyer.

20:27.852 --> 20:29.145
Okay.

20:31.356 --> 20:33.399
How are things with you?

20:34.359 --> 20:35.443
Everything's fine.

20:35.526 --> 20:36.611
Terrific!

20:36.694 --> 20:38.279
I got a job.

20:38.363 --> 20:39.447
Oh!

20:39.530 --> 20:40.573
I'm a...

20:40.657 --> 20:42.492
I'm a secretary.

20:44.327 --> 20:46.663
Well, how's Liza?

20:46.746 --> 20:49.165
Fine. She's waiting in the car.

20:51.876 --> 20:53.711
We‒We've got to go.

20:56.881 --> 20:58.341
Well, so long.

20:59.884 --> 21:01.135
Bye.

21:24.534 --> 21:28.496
I feel like I was
just here a minute ago.

21:28.579 --> 21:30.498
You'll get
used to it.

21:30.581 --> 21:31.666
Everybody does.

21:31.749 --> 21:32.875
Eventually.

21:46.222 --> 21:48.224
Medicinal purposes.

21:50.977 --> 21:52.395
Violet Newstead,
please hold.

21:52.478 --> 21:53.896
Violet Newstead,
please hold.

21:53.980 --> 21:55.398
Hi, this is Violet.

21:55.481 --> 21:58.401
Mel, no, no.
That's 210, net 30.

21:58.484 --> 21:59.902
Delivered in 9 days.

21:59.986 --> 22:04.407
That's 2% of 4,405.50 is...

22:04.490 --> 22:05.575
88.11.

22:05.658 --> 22:07.827
Oh, my pleasure, Mel.

22:07.910 --> 22:10.580
Violet Newstead,
please hold.
Hi, this is Violet.

22:10.663 --> 22:12.165
Charlotte,
I've got it right here.

22:12.248 --> 22:16.252
I was waiting for your call.
That route is...

22:16.336 --> 22:20.340
32 via Dixie Express.

22:20.423 --> 22:22.383
Don't worry.
I've got it under control.

22:22.467 --> 22:23.760
Okay. Bye-bye.

22:23.843 --> 22:25.094
Violet News‒
Come on, kids.

22:25.178 --> 22:28.181
No fighting.

22:28.264 --> 22:31.225
Believe me. There's more than one
peanut butter and banana
sandwich in the world.

22:31.309 --> 22:34.270
What did I say this morning?
Okay. Love you, too.

22:34.354 --> 22:37.273
No, I don't want to talk
to the dog. Bye-bye.

22:40.693 --> 22:43.112
Oh, hi, Judy.
How's everything going?

22:43.196 --> 22:45.198
Fine, thanks.

22:45.281 --> 22:46.783
How'd you like to have
lunch today?

22:46.866 --> 22:48.785
Well, I'm afraid
I can't, thanks.

22:48.868 --> 22:49.952
Maybe tomorrow.

22:50.036 --> 22:52.455
I know the cutest
little Italian restaurant

22:52.538 --> 22:55.458
just a hop, skip,
and a jump from here.

22:55.541 --> 22:57.460
I should stay
in the office

22:57.543 --> 22:58.961
and learn
the routine,

22:59.045 --> 23:00.213
but thanks anyway.

23:00.296 --> 23:02.256
Yeah, sure.

23:10.807 --> 23:13.059
You know, I just
don't get it, Dwayne.

23:13.142 --> 23:14.394
What's that, honey?

23:14.477 --> 23:18.898
I'm as nice
as I know how to be
to everyone at that office.

23:18.981 --> 23:23.277
Everybody treats me
like a bastard
at a family reunion.

23:23.361 --> 23:25.780
Well, come over here
and sit down.

23:25.863 --> 23:28.366
Well, that hurts my feelings.

23:28.449 --> 23:30.284
Where's my smile?
I don't have one.

23:30.368 --> 23:33.079
They're just jealous
'cause you're so pretty.

23:33.162 --> 23:34.580
They're not jealous.

23:34.664 --> 23:35.748
Mm-hmm.

23:35.832 --> 23:37.250
Now, where's my smile?

23:37.333 --> 23:39.252
I want you to smile, okay?

23:39.335 --> 23:41.504
You forget
all about them.

23:41.587 --> 23:45.007
I'm going to give you
a real warm reception.

23:45.091 --> 23:47.009
I just bet you will.

23:50.346 --> 23:51.889
Violet, a little coffee.

23:53.182 --> 23:54.308
Yes, sir.

24:15.204 --> 24:17.498
Yeah. What else?

24:17.582 --> 24:20.960
Did you have a chance
to look at the report
on color-coding of accounts?

24:21.043 --> 24:23.463
Last month.
I gave it to you.

24:23.546 --> 24:26.174
We could improve
efficiency 20%.

24:26.257 --> 24:27.675
Sure, I looked
into that.

24:27.758 --> 24:29.177
That needs
a little work.

24:29.260 --> 24:30.761
I'll get back
to you on that.

24:30.845 --> 24:33.598
Yeah. Mm-hmm.
Okay.

24:39.729 --> 24:40.771
Oh, Violet,

24:40.855 --> 24:42.607
I haven't heard
from you.

24:42.690 --> 24:44.233
Did you get
my memo?

24:44.317 --> 24:46.652
I did, Roz.
I tore right through it.

24:46.736 --> 24:47.653
Good.

24:47.737 --> 24:49.655
We must
clamp down hard

24:49.739 --> 24:51.657
on any signs
of unionization.

24:51.741 --> 24:55.286
Oh, here comes Mr. Hart
with Mr. Hinkle.

24:55.369 --> 24:58.122
Coming from you,
that means a lot.

24:58.206 --> 24:59.624
Hello, girls.
How's it going?

24:59.707 --> 25:00.625
Just fine.

25:00.708 --> 25:02.168
Hello, Mr. Hinkle.

25:02.251 --> 25:06.714
Roz, you'll be getting
a copy of this report
Frank just gave me.

25:06.797 --> 25:10.551
We're going to start
color-coding the accounts
from now on.

25:10.635 --> 25:13.554
Frank's done
a brilliant study
with efficiency.

25:13.638 --> 25:17.099
Really?
Congratulations,
Mr. Hart.

25:17.183 --> 25:18.059
Thanks, Roz.

25:18.142 --> 25:20.061
Was just‒just brilliant.

25:20.144 --> 25:22.688
You're a fine piece
of manpower, Frank.

25:22.772 --> 25:26.317
Any other reforms
you want to make
are fine with me.

25:26.400 --> 25:27.318
Thank you.

25:27.401 --> 25:28.736
This is your floor.

25:28.819 --> 25:31.072
You run it
as you please.

25:31.155 --> 25:32.156
Going up?

25:32.240 --> 25:34.450
No. We're going down.

25:36.869 --> 25:39.080
Oh, I can't believe
that man.

25:39.163 --> 25:40.581
He has no shame.

25:40.665 --> 25:43.251
He stood right there
and presented my idea

25:43.334 --> 25:44.752
to the company's
president

25:44.835 --> 25:46.254
like it was his own.

25:46.337 --> 25:47.755
Why didn't you
call him on it?

25:47.838 --> 25:50.591
Oh, because
I'm playing it safe, damn it.

25:50.675 --> 25:54.595
In six weeks,
he makes the decision
about that promotion,

25:54.679 --> 25:57.431
and until then,
I'm playing
the good girl.

25:57.515 --> 25:58.766
You finished
up there?

25:58.849 --> 25:59.767
Yeah.

25:59.850 --> 26:00.768
Nice job.

26:00.851 --> 26:02.228
Thanks.

26:02.311 --> 26:05.231
Can you imagine
a mature woman
with four kids

26:05.314 --> 26:07.066
installing
a garage door opener,

26:07.149 --> 26:09.569
he still refers to me
as his girl.

26:09.652 --> 26:11.737
Mom, you gotta relax.

26:11.821 --> 26:14.240
I'm going to
roll you a joint.

26:14.323 --> 26:16.742
Josh, you know how
I feel about that.

26:16.826 --> 26:19.245
Besides, your grandmother
will pitch a fit

26:19.328 --> 26:21.747
if she even hears you
mention marijuana.

26:21.831 --> 26:24.250
She doesn't understand
moderation.

26:24.333 --> 26:26.752
Besides, you're
the one that keeps
talking about

26:26.836 --> 26:28.754
"harm springs
from excess," right?

26:28.838 --> 26:30.256
Okay. Yes, I know.

26:30.339 --> 26:32.258
I'm talking
about one joint.

26:32.341 --> 26:34.760
Okay.
I don't like it, Josh.

26:34.844 --> 26:38.264
How long have you
been waiting
for this promotion?

26:38.347 --> 26:40.766
Slip it in my purse.

26:40.850 --> 26:41.767
It works!

26:41.851 --> 26:43.102
You did it.

26:49.442 --> 26:50.443
What?

26:50.526 --> 26:52.612
Don't go flying
off the handle.

26:52.695 --> 26:55.406
You gave that promotion
to Bob Enright?

26:55.489 --> 26:57.950
I've got five years
seniority over him.

26:58.034 --> 26:58.951
I know.

26:59.035 --> 27:00.119
Christ,
I trained him.

27:00.202 --> 27:02.413
I know, but see,
the company‒

27:02.496 --> 27:03.873
Oh, the company,
bullshit.

27:03.956 --> 27:06.459
You promoted him.
You tell me why.

27:06.542 --> 27:10.254
Well, in the first place,
Bob does have
a college degree.

27:10.338 --> 27:11.255
Oh, brilliant.

27:11.339 --> 27:13.049
While he's
away at college

27:13.132 --> 27:14.550
getting
his useless degree,

27:14.634 --> 27:16.427
I'm working
my butt off.

27:16.510 --> 27:19.430
In the second place,
he's supporting a family.

27:19.513 --> 27:20.723
And I don't?

27:20.806 --> 27:23.225
What's that
got to do
with anything?

27:23.309 --> 27:24.560
My hands are tied.

27:24.644 --> 27:26.896
The company needs
a man in this position.

27:26.979 --> 27:29.565
Clients would rather
deal with men
about figures.

27:29.649 --> 27:31.233
Now we're getting at it.

27:31.317 --> 27:34.236
I lose a promotion
because of some
idiot prejudice.

27:34.320 --> 27:36.155
The boys in the club
are threatened,

27:36.238 --> 27:39.659
and you're
intimidated by any woman that
won't sit at the back of the bus.

27:39.742 --> 27:42.244
Spare me the women's
lib crap, okay?

27:42.328 --> 27:44.413
I know your feelings.
I understand.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.415
You understand zilch.

27:46.499 --> 27:48.918
I understand
I'm still the boss here,

27:49.001 --> 27:50.920
and though you
have your value,

27:51.003 --> 27:53.589
you better get
hold of yourself.

27:53.673 --> 27:55.091
God damn it.

27:55.174 --> 27:56.592
Doralee, get in here!

27:56.676 --> 27:57.593
Okay.

27:57.677 --> 27:59.595
I told you
to have this chair fixed.

27:59.679 --> 28:01.430
Okay,
I'm going to leave,

28:01.514 --> 28:03.516
but I'm telling you
one thing‒

28:03.599 --> 28:06.936
Don't you ever
refer to me as
your girl again.

28:07.019 --> 28:08.688
What are you
talking about?

28:09.772 --> 28:11.691
Doralee,
what's with this chair?

28:11.774 --> 28:13.192
I'll tell you‒

28:13.275 --> 28:15.361
I'm no girl.
I'm a woman.

28:15.444 --> 28:16.487
You hear?

28:16.570 --> 28:19.198
I'm not your wife
or your mother...

28:19.281 --> 28:20.700
or even
your mistress.

28:20.783 --> 28:22.535
What?

28:22.618 --> 28:24.036
I am your employee,

28:24.120 --> 28:27.540
and as such,
I expect to be treated equally,

28:27.623 --> 28:30.793
with a little dignity
and a little respect.

28:30.876 --> 28:33.045
What do you mean,
mistress?

28:33.129 --> 28:34.505
She's just upset.

28:34.588 --> 28:36.340
Doralee, the whole
company knows

28:36.424 --> 28:38.551
you two are
having an affair.

28:38.634 --> 28:40.886
Who's been saying
we're having an affair?

28:40.970 --> 28:42.388
Who's been saying it?

28:42.471 --> 28:43.764
He has.

28:46.308 --> 28:47.351
What?

28:49.812 --> 28:51.897
Violet, where
are you going?

28:51.981 --> 28:53.566
I'm going
to get drunk.

28:53.649 --> 28:55.901
Atta girl.

28:55.985 --> 28:57.403
You've been
telling everybody

28:57.486 --> 28:59.238
I'm sleeping
with you, huh?

28:59.321 --> 29:01.240
Well, that's why
these people

29:01.323 --> 29:02.700
treat me
like some floozy.

29:02.783 --> 29:04.744
They think
I'm screwing the boss.

29:04.827 --> 29:06.746
That's not it at all‒

29:06.829 --> 29:08.706
You just love it,
don't you?

29:08.789 --> 29:10.583
Gives you some
cheap thrill,

29:10.666 --> 29:12.084
like knocking over
pencils‒

29:12.168 --> 29:13.502
Let's don't get exc‒

29:13.586 --> 29:15.713
Get your
scummy hands off me.

29:15.796 --> 29:18.090
I've been
straight with you
since I got here.

29:18.174 --> 29:20.885
I put up with
your pinching

29:20.968 --> 29:22.386
'cause I need this job,

29:22.470 --> 29:24.388
but this is
the last straw!

29:24.472 --> 29:25.848
Let's just‒

29:25.931 --> 29:28.309
I got a gun
in my purse.

29:28.392 --> 29:32.229
I've been forgiving
because of the way
I was brought up,

29:32.313 --> 29:35.232
but if you ever say
another word about me

29:35.316 --> 29:36.734
or make another
indecent proposal,

29:36.817 --> 29:38.235
I'll get that gun,

29:38.319 --> 29:41.822
and I'll change you
from a rooster to a hen
with one shot!

29:42.823 --> 29:45.242
Don't think
I can't do it!

29:49.163 --> 29:50.289
Shit.

29:54.502 --> 29:55.753
Where are you going?

29:55.836 --> 29:57.588
I need a drink, Roz.

29:57.671 --> 30:00.257
I'm taking the rest
of the day off.

30:01.467 --> 30:02.927
Atta girl.

30:05.346 --> 30:07.264
What do you want?
I'm busy.

30:07.348 --> 30:10.267
I wouldn't
disturb you if this
weren't important,

30:10.351 --> 30:12.770
but I just heard
one of the girls

30:12.853 --> 30:14.271
commit a serious
infraction.

30:14.355 --> 30:15.314
What?

30:15.397 --> 30:17.775
Maria Delgado
was speaking
to a girl

30:17.858 --> 30:19.610
whose voice
I didn't recognize

30:19.693 --> 30:22.613
when I overheard her
reveal her salary

30:22.696 --> 30:26.075
and make estimates
of yours and mine.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.828
Get rid of her.
Dismiss her.

30:28.911 --> 30:31.497
It isn't as if
she hasn't
been warned.

