50:34.032 --> 50:35.450
I hope it's
not serious.

50:35.533 --> 50:36.451
Me, neither.

50:36.534 --> 50:37.952
Well, maybe
a little serious.

50:38.036 --> 50:41.956
Some trifle that'll
keep him out for
the next 20 years.

50:42.040 --> 50:42.957
Let's go.

50:43.041 --> 50:44.959
I'll meet you
at the elevator.

50:45.043 --> 50:45.960
Okay.

50:53.718 --> 50:55.136
Oh, my God!

50:57.722 --> 50:59.307
Oh, my God.

50:59.390 --> 51:00.600
Ahh.

51:03.644 --> 51:05.313
Oh.

51:06.939 --> 51:07.857
Violet,

51:07.940 --> 51:10.151
isn't it awful
about Mr. Hart?

51:10.234 --> 51:11.694
How did it happen,
Roz?

51:11.778 --> 51:15.323
Fell and hit his head
on the credenza.

51:15.406 --> 51:16.824
What about
the coffee?

51:16.908 --> 51:17.825
What?

51:17.909 --> 51:19.327
Where is the coffee cup?

51:19.410 --> 51:20.328
Oh, here.

51:20.411 --> 51:22.747
It was by him
on the floor.

51:22.830 --> 51:25.541
He must've been
drinking it
when he blacked out.

51:25.625 --> 51:26.542
What hospital?

51:26.626 --> 51:28.086
St. Ambrose.

51:28.169 --> 51:29.128
Oh.

51:29.212 --> 51:30.671
Oh, my God.

51:32.965 --> 51:35.176
I know you feel.

51:35.259 --> 51:37.095
Aah. Aah.

51:37.178 --> 51:38.137
Judy.

51:38.221 --> 51:40.139
Oh, Judy.
Hurry. Hurry.

51:40.223 --> 51:41.641
What's the matter?

51:41.724 --> 51:43.142
Something terrible's
happened.

51:43.226 --> 51:44.685
You won't
believe it.

51:45.770 --> 51:47.188
I don't believe it.

51:47.271 --> 51:49.690
How could you make
such a stupid mistake?

51:49.774 --> 51:51.984
I thought it was
Skinny and Sweet.

51:52.068 --> 51:53.486
Here, look.
They're identical,

51:53.569 --> 51:56.447
except for
the skull and crossbones
on the label.

51:56.531 --> 51:57.949
Someone's
going to see you.

51:58.032 --> 51:59.909
I've got to
go to the hospital.

51:59.992 --> 52:02.078
They'll have to
pump his stomach.

52:02.161 --> 52:03.830
Don't be hysterical.
Don't be hysterical.

52:03.913 --> 52:05.873
You're right.
Keep calm. Keep calm.

52:17.677 --> 52:19.595
You'd better speak
to admitting, ma'am.

52:19.679 --> 52:20.596
Yeah. Right.

52:27.353 --> 52:28.771
My boss was
brought in.

52:28.855 --> 52:30.189
Franklin Hart.

52:34.902 --> 52:36.320
There we go.

52:41.993 --> 52:43.327
What's go‒

52:43.411 --> 52:44.829
What's going on?

52:44.912 --> 52:47.456
Take it easy now.
You blacked out.

52:47.540 --> 52:49.083
How do you feel?

52:49.167 --> 52:50.585
I feel fine.

52:50.668 --> 52:53.963
I fell off a chair
and hit my head.

52:54.046 --> 52:55.298
Uh-huh.

52:55.381 --> 52:56.299
Ooh.

52:56.382 --> 52:58.259
You got quite
a bump there.

52:58.342 --> 53:01.179
I think we'll take you
upstairs for X-rays.

53:01.262 --> 53:02.180
X-rays?

53:02.263 --> 53:03.973
Mm-hmm.

53:04.056 --> 53:05.474
Wait a minute, doc.

53:05.558 --> 53:07.476
I don't want
any X-rays.

53:07.560 --> 53:08.769
I like my head.

53:08.853 --> 53:10.813
We ought to do some tests.

53:10.897 --> 53:12.315
You do tests
on yourself.

53:12.398 --> 53:14.859
I know what you guys
racket is.

53:14.942 --> 53:17.361
You're not
suckering me
into hospital bills,

53:17.445 --> 53:19.739
not for a little
bump on the head.

53:19.822 --> 53:21.866
Hey, doc.
Cardiac arrest.

53:21.949 --> 53:23.367
He stopped breathing.

53:23.451 --> 53:26.370
Open his shirt.
Plug him into
the monitor.

53:27.997 --> 53:31.125
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

53:31.209 --> 53:32.585
1, 2.

53:41.469 --> 53:43.221
Hurry.

53:44.347 --> 53:47.391
2, 3, 4, 5.

53:47.475 --> 53:51.145
1, 2, 3, 4.

53:52.813 --> 53:53.981
That bum.

53:55.066 --> 53:56.692
He was our
only witness.

53:56.776 --> 53:58.527
We had him all ready
to testify.

53:58.611 --> 53:59.904
Now this.

54:01.864 --> 54:02.782
There's Doralee.

54:02.865 --> 54:03.783
Doralee.

54:03.866 --> 54:05.284
What are you
doing here?

54:05.368 --> 54:06.744
Doralee, something
terrible has happened.

54:06.827 --> 54:07.745
What?

54:07.828 --> 54:09.747
Violet put poison
in Hart's coffee.

54:09.830 --> 54:11.207
It was an accident.

54:11.290 --> 54:12.708
You mean,
that's why‒

54:12.792 --> 54:15.169
It looks just like
Skinny and Sweet.

54:15.253 --> 54:16.212
Good grief.

54:16.295 --> 54:17.713
Where is he?

54:17.797 --> 54:20.549
The emergency room.
First door
on the right.

54:20.633 --> 54:22.718
Oh, my God.
There's a policeman.

54:22.802 --> 54:25.721
What's he doing here?

54:25.805 --> 54:27.265
I don't know.

54:27.348 --> 54:30.101
The guy on the gurney,
how is he?

54:30.184 --> 54:31.602
He's not so good.

54:31.686 --> 54:33.813
Can I speak
to the doctor?

54:33.896 --> 54:35.773
He knows
you're here.

54:35.856 --> 54:37.275
He knows I'm here.

54:37.358 --> 54:39.819
Oh, my God.
They found out already.

54:39.902 --> 54:41.279
Don't panic.
Please don't panic.

54:41.362 --> 54:43.072
How is he, doc?

54:43.155 --> 54:44.573
Ah, he's dead.

54:44.657 --> 54:45.616
Aw.

54:45.700 --> 54:47.743
Oh, my God.

54:47.827 --> 54:49.203
Can you tell
what caused it?

54:49.287 --> 54:50.955
Not without
an autopsy.

54:51.038 --> 54:53.457
You fellows can
come into my office.

54:53.541 --> 54:55.459
I'm fairly certain
it was poison.

54:55.543 --> 54:56.460
Poison?

54:56.544 --> 54:57.628
Ahh.

54:57.712 --> 55:00.589
It's okay.
It's okay.

55:00.673 --> 55:01.549
Easy now.

55:01.632 --> 55:02.550
Poison.

55:02.633 --> 55:03.551
Poison.

55:03.634 --> 55:05.052
It's all over.

55:05.136 --> 55:06.554
Did you hear‒
an autopsy?

55:06.637 --> 55:09.974
I'll save them the trouble
and give them the poison.

55:10.057 --> 55:10.975
Violet!

55:11.058 --> 55:12.893
You want someone
to see it?

55:12.977 --> 55:14.395
Who cares?
I'm finished.

55:14.478 --> 55:15.813
I'm a murderer.

55:15.896 --> 55:17.315
No, you're not.

55:17.398 --> 55:19.108
I'm a murderess.

55:19.191 --> 55:20.609
My poor kids.

55:20.693 --> 55:22.111
Violet, you're nothing
until proven guilty.

55:22.194 --> 55:25.323
They'll find
the poison when
they do the autopsy.

55:25.406 --> 55:27.325
I'll get rid
of the poison.

55:27.408 --> 55:29.327
I'll get rid
of the body.

55:29.410 --> 55:31.829
No, it's not murder.
They're are extenuating
circumstances.

55:31.912 --> 55:33.497
It was an accident.

55:33.581 --> 55:34.665
An accident?

55:34.749 --> 55:37.043
She was thinking
about doing it
last night.

55:37.126 --> 55:39.045
We all thought
about it.

55:39.128 --> 55:41.047
She didn't do it
on purpose.

55:41.130 --> 55:42.548
Oh, maybe
unconsciously I did.

55:42.631 --> 55:45.426
I'm going to the pen.

55:45.509 --> 55:47.345
Let's get
her a lawyer.

55:47.428 --> 55:49.180
I'll be locked up for life.
Where's the phone?

55:49.263 --> 55:50.514
Over there.

55:50.598 --> 55:51.974
Do you have
any change?

55:52.058 --> 55:53.976
I'm going to
lose my job.

55:54.060 --> 55:54.977
Calm down.

55:55.061 --> 55:56.479
I've killed the boss.

55:56.562 --> 55:58.981
You think they're not going to
fire me for that?

55:59.065 --> 56:01.609
Hush. Now just sit here.
We'll be right back.

56:17.708 --> 56:20.961
Oh, medic,
this the guy
for the autopsy?

56:21.045 --> 56:21.962
Yeah.

56:22.046 --> 56:24.465
The doctor would
like to see you.

56:24.548 --> 56:26.133
Right this way.

57:29.864 --> 57:32.199
They're looking for
a second opinion.

57:32.283 --> 57:33.659
I'm going to
go ahead.

57:33.742 --> 57:37.705
So, look, if you can
get it to them by Friday...

58:21.999 --> 58:22.666
Ma'am.
Ohh!

58:22.750 --> 58:25.503
Excuse me. Where's
the coffee shop?

58:25.586 --> 58:26.504
What?

58:26.587 --> 58:28.005
The coffee shop.

58:28.088 --> 58:29.507
The coffee shop?

58:29.590 --> 58:31.258
No. I'm new here.

58:31.342 --> 58:34.470
I'm new here, too.
Where do you work?

58:34.553 --> 58:35.513
Downstairs.

58:35.596 --> 58:37.348
The morgue?

58:37.431 --> 58:38.307
That's right.

58:38.390 --> 58:39.308
He's...

58:39.391 --> 58:40.809
Yes, he is.

58:40.893 --> 58:41.810
How?

58:41.894 --> 58:43.604
Coffee,
too much coffee.

58:43.687 --> 58:46.106
I'm just taking him
out for some air‒

58:46.190 --> 58:49.193
Air for me.
He's coming along
for the ride.

58:50.819 --> 58:52.279
You're a doctor.

58:52.363 --> 58:53.822
I didn't see
your badge.

58:53.906 --> 58:54.782
Sorry.

58:54.865 --> 58:56.033
I'm a doctor.

58:56.116 --> 58:57.576
Why am I talking
to you?

58:57.660 --> 58:58.619
Piss off.

59:04.416 --> 59:05.292
How's Violet?

59:13.300 --> 59:16.387
Oh, honey, I think
Violet has flipped out.

59:50.671 --> 59:52.131
Violet,
what are you doing?

59:52.214 --> 59:54.133
Come on,
get in. Get in.

59:54.216 --> 59:56.927
There's no time
for talking. Get in.

01:00:00.139 --> 01:00:03.100
Violet, slow down.

01:00:03.183 --> 01:00:04.560
Why are you
driving fast?

01:00:04.643 --> 01:00:07.104
They can't
do an autopsy
without a body.

01:00:07.187 --> 01:00:08.772
I told you
she's flipped.

01:00:08.856 --> 01:00:11.442
She has just
absolutely flipped.

01:00:11.525 --> 01:00:13.110
Where is the body?

01:00:13.193 --> 01:00:14.570
In the trunk.

01:00:14.653 --> 01:00:16.071
We'll get
cement blocks

01:00:16.155 --> 01:00:18.282
and pitch him
off the pier.

01:00:18.365 --> 01:00:19.783
No one will
ever know.

01:00:19.867 --> 01:00:20.784
You're crazy.

01:00:20.868 --> 01:00:22.620
They always find it.

01:00:22.703 --> 01:00:24.079
Oh, crazy, am I?

01:00:24.163 --> 01:00:25.748
They never found
Jimmy Hoffa.

01:00:25.831 --> 01:00:27.583
Slow down.

01:00:27.666 --> 01:00:29.543
Will you just
slow down?

01:00:29.627 --> 01:00:31.629
Let's not panic.
Let's not panic.

01:00:31.712 --> 01:00:33.130
There's a restaurant
up there.

01:00:33.213 --> 01:00:35.633
Why don't we pull over
and stop for a bite?

01:00:35.716 --> 01:00:38.969
How can you
think of food
at a time like this?

01:00:39.053 --> 01:00:40.512
I'm not thinking
of food.

01:00:40.596 --> 01:00:42.056
I'm not hungry.

01:00:50.022 --> 01:00:51.482
Violet,
we're not criminal.

01:00:51.565 --> 01:00:53.817
You're not a criminal.
It was an accident.

01:00:53.901 --> 01:00:55.444
Well, we're
criminals now.

01:00:55.527 --> 01:00:57.946
We've just
stolen a corpse
from a hospital.

01:00:58.030 --> 01:00:59.448
That sounds like
criminal to me.

01:00:59.531 --> 01:01:02.493
We'll just turn around
and take it back.

01:01:02.576 --> 01:01:04.161
We'll get caught.

01:01:04.244 --> 01:01:06.163
You think they'll
listen to us?

01:01:06.246 --> 01:01:07.665
Will you please
stop arguing?

01:01:07.748 --> 01:01:10.501
Think about
where we can get
some cement.

01:01:14.755 --> 01:01:16.632
Look out!

01:01:16.715 --> 01:01:18.759
Don't panic. Don't panic.

01:01:22.221 --> 01:01:23.597
Aah.
Aah.
Aah.

01:01:27.518 --> 01:01:28.936
What happened?

01:01:29.019 --> 01:01:29.978
She panicked.

01:01:30.062 --> 01:01:31.021
Nobody's hurt.

01:01:31.105 --> 01:01:32.898
It's just a little accident.

01:01:32.981 --> 01:01:35.567
We'll be out
of here in no time.

01:01:37.528 --> 01:01:39.446
The front fender's
hitting the tire.

01:01:39.530 --> 01:01:42.449
Oh, good Lord. Get out.
Let's look at it.

01:01:46.870 --> 01:01:48.288
Oh, that ain't
too bad.

01:01:48.372 --> 01:01:50.374
We'll pull
that fender out.

01:01:50.457 --> 01:01:51.875
Give me a hand.

01:01:51.959 --> 01:01:53.460
Oh, God.

01:01:53.544 --> 01:01:55.129
Wait. That's no use.

01:01:55.212 --> 01:01:57.089
We need a crowbar
or something.

01:01:57.172 --> 01:02:00.134
There's a tire iron
in the trunk.

01:02:07.474 --> 01:02:09.393
Judy, turn
the blinkers off.

01:02:26.452 --> 01:02:31.123
Uh, Judy, would
you come back here
for a second?

01:02:35.502 --> 01:02:36.420
What?

01:02:36.503 --> 01:02:38.922
Look.

01:02:39.006 --> 01:02:39.923
Who's that?

01:02:40.007 --> 01:02:41.425
I don't know.

01:02:41.508 --> 01:02:42.426
Where's Hart?

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:44.595
I don't know.

01:02:44.678 --> 01:02:47.389
Oh, my God.
You mean, she‒

01:02:47.473 --> 01:02:49.391
Oh, my God!

01:02:51.643 --> 01:02:56.774
Violet, honey,
would you come over here
for a second?

01:02:56.857 --> 01:02:58.734
What is the matter
with you?

01:02:58.817 --> 01:03:00.235
We have got
to get the‒

01:03:00.319 --> 01:03:01.236
Who is that?

01:03:01.320 --> 01:03:03.405
I don't know.

01:03:03.489 --> 01:03:05.949
What do you mean
you don't know?

01:03:06.033 --> 01:03:07.826
What happened
to Hart's body?

01:03:07.910 --> 01:03:11.121
It's not here.
You think it walked away?

01:03:11.205 --> 01:03:12.080
But I‒

01:03:12.164 --> 01:03:13.582
Violet,
how could you?

01:03:13.665 --> 01:03:15.083
How could you?

01:03:15.167 --> 01:03:17.795
I guess I must have
made a mistake.

01:03:17.878 --> 01:03:19.755
You steal
the wrong body,

01:03:19.838 --> 01:03:22.633
and all you can say
is, "I made a mistake."

01:03:22.716 --> 01:03:24.134
It could happen
to anyone.

01:03:24.218 --> 01:03:26.136
Oh, this is awful.

01:03:26.220 --> 01:03:27.679
It's so improper.

01:03:27.763 --> 01:03:29.181
It's so disrespectful.

01:03:29.264 --> 01:03:30.891
He's dead.
He doesn't mind.

01:03:30.974 --> 01:03:32.893
There's nothing to
get excited about.

01:03:32.976 --> 01:03:34.478
We'll just take it back.

01:03:34.561 --> 01:03:35.479
What?

01:03:35.562 --> 01:03:38.148
No harm's done.
We'll take it back.

01:03:38.232 --> 01:03:39.316
That's great.

01:03:39.399 --> 01:03:42.820
We waltz in there and
say, "we made a mistake."

01:03:42.903 --> 01:03:45.280
Maybe they'll give us
Hart's body in exchange.

01:03:45.364 --> 01:03:47.115
There's no need
to get sarcastic.

01:03:47.199 --> 01:03:49.117
You took it.
You take it back.

01:03:49.201 --> 01:03:50.077
Stop it.

01:03:50.160 --> 01:03:51.495
We're all
in this together.

01:03:51.578 --> 01:03:53.956
Now we have
to be very calm.

01:03:54.039 --> 01:03:55.958
We're going to
fix the fender.

01:03:56.041 --> 01:03:57.960
We'll go back
to the hospital.

01:03:58.043 --> 01:04:00.963
We'll figure
out a plan to
drop off the body.

01:04:01.046 --> 01:04:03.715
Then we'll decide
what we're
going to do next.

01:04:03.799 --> 01:04:05.759
I tried to tell
this woman‒

01:04:05.843 --> 01:04:07.594
Will you two shut up?

01:04:33.579 --> 01:04:34.997
It's not a bad plan.

01:04:35.080 --> 01:04:36.498
It might work.

01:04:36.582 --> 01:04:39.001
If we could just
find a wheelchair.

01:04:39.084 --> 01:04:42.004
I saw a couple
outside the emergency
entrance before.

01:04:42.087 --> 01:04:43.922
I think
that's a good idea.

01:04:44.006 --> 01:04:46.925
I just wish we knew
what happened to Hart.

01:04:47.009 --> 01:04:49.469
We're going to
find out soon enough.

01:04:52.472 --> 01:04:55.058
What's that?

01:04:55.142 --> 01:04:57.769
It's a siren.

01:04:57.853 --> 01:04:59.313
It's a policeman.

01:04:59.396 --> 01:05:01.106
He wants us
to pull over.

01:05:01.189 --> 01:05:03.483
Do I make
a break for it?

01:05:03.567 --> 01:05:05.110
I've got my gun.

01:05:05.193 --> 01:05:06.528
Are you crazy?

01:05:06.612 --> 01:05:08.030
Oh, my God.

01:05:08.113 --> 01:05:10.032
Don't panic.
Don't panic.

01:05:10.115 --> 01:05:11.158
What does he want?

01:05:11.241 --> 01:05:13.869
I don't know.
Pull over.

01:05:13.952 --> 01:05:16.079
Pull over.
Be ready for anything.

01:05:16.163 --> 01:05:18.582
Listen to what he says
and don't panic.

01:05:18.665 --> 01:05:20.083
But what if he wants‒

01:05:20.167 --> 01:05:22.794
For Christ's sake,
pull over! Pull over!

01:05:37.267 --> 01:05:38.435
Good evening, ladies.

01:05:38.518 --> 01:05:40.938
May I see
your license and
registration, please?

01:05:41.021 --> 01:05:42.439
Why? I wasn't speeding.

01:05:42.522 --> 01:05:43.899
I didn't say
you were.

01:05:43.982 --> 01:05:45.275
Your taillight
is blinking.

01:05:45.359 --> 01:05:46.276
It is?

01:05:46.360 --> 01:05:49.112
Are your signals on?

01:05:49.196 --> 01:05:50.113
No.

01:05:50.197 --> 01:05:52.240
There's a short
in the trunk.

01:05:52.324 --> 01:05:53.742
A short in the trunk?

01:05:53.825 --> 01:05:56.703
We've got a short
in the trunk.

01:05:56.787 --> 01:05:58.205
Probably just
a defective wire.

01:05:58.288 --> 01:05:59.873
You want
to take a look?

01:05:59.957 --> 01:06:01.792
Do we want
to take a look?

01:06:01.875 --> 01:06:04.795
No, we can't, Officer.
We don't have time.

01:06:04.878 --> 01:06:06.296
We're on an emergency.

01:06:06.380 --> 01:06:08.465
That's‒that's right.
She's a doctor.

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:09.800
Oh, you're
a doctor?

01:06:09.883 --> 01:06:12.678
What do think I am,
a beautician?

01:06:12.761 --> 01:06:14.137
I didn't see
your badge.

01:06:14.221 --> 01:06:15.639
What's
the trouble?

01:06:15.722 --> 01:06:19.309
I'm taking this woman
to the hospital,
and she's sick.

01:06:19.393 --> 01:06:21.061
Which one
of you is sick?

01:06:21.144 --> 01:06:22.771
I am.
I am.

01:06:22.854 --> 01:06:24.481
She is.
She is.

01:06:24.564 --> 01:06:27.109
They're both sick.

01:06:28.568 --> 01:06:32.155
What is that
you're hiding there?

01:06:32.239 --> 01:06:33.156
What? This?

01:06:33.240 --> 01:06:34.157
Yes.

01:06:34.241 --> 01:06:35.659
It's rat poison.

01:06:35.742 --> 01:06:37.160
She ate it.

01:06:37.244 --> 01:06:38.245
What?

01:06:38.328 --> 01:06:40.831
She ate
the rat poison.
That's why they're sick.

01:06:40.914 --> 01:06:42.290
You ate the rat poison?

01:06:42.374 --> 01:06:44.668
I thought it was
Skinny and Sweet.

01:06:44.751 --> 01:06:47.170
It looks just like
Skinny and Sweet,

01:06:47.254 --> 01:06:50.632
except for the little
skull and crossbones
on the label.

01:06:50.716 --> 01:06:52.134
Can we go now,
Officer?

01:06:52.217 --> 01:06:53.844
I'm not feeling very well.

01:06:53.927 --> 01:06:55.345
Did you hear that?

01:06:55.429 --> 01:06:56.847
She's not feeling
very well.

01:06:56.930 --> 01:06:58.640
I've got a dying woman,

01:06:58.724 --> 01:07:01.059
and you want to look
for a short.

01:07:01.143 --> 01:07:03.562
I'm sorry.
If we don't
make it on time,

01:07:03.645 --> 01:07:05.063
I'm holding you
responsible.

01:07:05.147 --> 01:07:06.064
Don't worry.

01:07:06.148 --> 01:07:07.566
I'll give you
an escort.

01:07:07.649 --> 01:07:08.567
An escort?

01:07:08.650 --> 01:07:11.194
He's going to
give us an escort.

01:07:11.278 --> 01:07:12.863
Oh, Lord.

01:07:12.946 --> 01:07:13.822
Hang on‒

01:07:13.905 --> 01:07:16.408
Forget it, Mac.
We can't wait.

01:07:31.715 --> 01:07:33.133
How did it go?

01:07:33.216 --> 01:07:35.135
I couldn't find out
about Hart.

01:07:35.218 --> 01:07:37.721
They don't know,
or they won't tell us.

01:07:37.804 --> 01:07:39.222
What are we
going to do?

01:07:39.306 --> 01:07:40.307
Nothing.

01:07:40.390 --> 01:07:42.768
We're going to wait
until they come to us.

01:07:42.851 --> 01:07:44.728
Go to the office
in the morning

01:07:44.811 --> 01:07:46.730
and pretend like
nothing has happened.

01:07:48.190 --> 01:07:50.108
Well, what about
the other matter?

01:07:50.192 --> 01:07:51.651
Don't worry about it.

01:07:53.236 --> 01:07:55.155
It's been taken care of.

01:08:17.010 --> 01:08:17.928
Hey, Viv.

01:08:18.011 --> 01:08:21.723
We got another stiff
in the john.

01:08:30.023 --> 01:08:32.274
Morning, Judy.

01:08:32.359 --> 01:08:34.444
Morning, Violet.

01:08:34.528 --> 01:08:36.446
Doralee, uh,
no calls this morning.

01:08:36.529 --> 01:08:39.491
I don't want to be
disturbed at all.

01:08:47.666 --> 01:08:50.042
All that running
around last night
was useless.

01:08:50.127 --> 01:08:53.087
Hart left with
a little bump
on his head.

01:08:53.171 --> 01:08:55.590
I did put the poison
in the coffee.

01:08:55.674 --> 01:08:57.091
I know it.

01:08:57.175 --> 01:08:59.678
Well, he absolutely
did not drink it, Violet.

01:08:59.761 --> 01:09:01.680
How could we
be so stupid?

01:09:01.763 --> 01:09:04.224
Did anybody
think to look
under the stalls.

01:09:04.307 --> 01:09:06.225
Yes. Yes.
And there's nobody there.

01:09:06.309 --> 01:09:08.645
Look, I propose we forget
the whole thing.

01:09:08.728 --> 01:09:10.147
It never happened.

01:09:10.229 --> 01:09:11.648
That's okay with me.

01:09:11.731 --> 01:09:13.483
I'll never
mention it again.

01:09:13.567 --> 01:09:14.984
Thank God
it's Friday.

01:09:15.068 --> 01:09:16.987
Why don't we start
the weekend

01:09:17.069 --> 01:09:18.488
with a drink
at Charlie's?

01:09:18.572 --> 01:09:20.657
You know,
we are so lucky.

01:09:20.740 --> 01:09:23.326
I'm glad this whole
mess is finally over.

01:09:23.410 --> 01:09:25.120
Oh, me, too.

01:09:35.921 --> 01:09:37.299
Is this accurate?

01:09:37.381 --> 01:09:38.800
They actually
said this?

01:09:38.884 --> 01:09:40.801
Clearly as I could
make out.

01:09:40.886 --> 01:09:42.804
My notes were
a little fuzzy.

01:09:42.888 --> 01:09:44.723
Well, this is
very interesting.

01:09:44.805 --> 01:09:48.225
Stealing corpses,
eluding the police.

01:09:48.310 --> 01:09:50.729
May-Maybe they knew
you were hiding,

01:09:50.812 --> 01:09:52.647
just‒just pulling
your leg.

01:09:52.731 --> 01:09:54.232
I don't think so.

01:09:54.316 --> 01:09:59.404
In any event, I think
you should be aware of
that coffee business.

01:09:59.487 --> 01:10:03.867
Yeah. I think
I can use that
to some advantage.

01:10:03.950 --> 01:10:05.368
Whoo! Look out,
Charlie's,

01:10:05.452 --> 01:10:06.870
here we come.

01:10:06.953 --> 01:10:08.872
Oh, Judy.
Wait just a second.

01:10:08.955 --> 01:10:10.457
I'll be right back.

01:10:10.540 --> 01:10:12.000
I'll‒I'll tell Violet.

01:10:13.752 --> 01:10:15.962
It's 5:00, Mr. Hart.
You wanted to see me?

01:10:16.046 --> 01:10:16.963
I did, Doralee.

01:10:17.047 --> 01:10:20.008
I'd like you to come over
to my house tonight.

01:10:20.091 --> 01:10:23.970
I'm not working
tonight.
This is Friday.

01:10:24.054 --> 01:10:26.223
Who said anything
about work?

01:10:27.849 --> 01:10:29.768
Oh, uh, by the way,

01:10:29.851 --> 01:10:32.103
have you ever
heard of strychnine?

01:10:32.187 --> 01:10:34.606
Strychnine
is a poison, I think.

01:10:34.689 --> 01:10:36.233
Yes, it is a poison.

01:10:36.316 --> 01:10:38.193
I just talked to
the hospital.

01:10:38.276 --> 01:10:40.237
They found
traces of strychnine

01:10:40.320 --> 01:10:42.948
when they pumped out
my stomach yesterday.

01:10:43.031 --> 01:10:45.575
What? You told me
you just hit your head.

01:10:45.659 --> 01:10:49.496
I had to be sure.
I think you need
evidence like that

01:10:49.579 --> 01:10:51.915
if you're going to
accuse somebody of murder.

01:10:51.998 --> 01:10:52.999
Murder?

01:10:53.083 --> 01:10:53.917
Yeah.

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:56.419
You and Violet
and that girl Judy

01:10:56.503 --> 01:10:57.921
tried to murder me
yesterday.

01:10:58.004 --> 01:11:00.882
Put the rat poison
in my coffee.

01:11:00.966 --> 01:11:03.385
Oh, my goodness.
I don't believe this.

01:11:03.468 --> 01:11:05.387
It was all a big mistake.

01:11:05.470 --> 01:11:06.888
That's very good.

01:11:06.972 --> 01:11:09.891
You should be scared,
because I know
all about it.

01:11:09.975 --> 01:11:12.894
All I have to do
is call the police.

01:11:12.978 --> 01:11:14.896
It really
was a mistake.

01:11:14.980 --> 01:11:17.899
Violet put the poison in
strictly by accident.

01:11:17.983 --> 01:11:20.360
She might get a jury
to believe that.

01:11:20.443 --> 01:11:21.861
Then again, she might not.

01:11:21.945 --> 01:11:24.698
But the big question here
is whether or not

01:11:24.781 --> 01:11:25.949
you want to take
that chance.

01:11:26.032 --> 01:11:28.118
What are you
driving at?

01:11:28.201 --> 01:11:29.619
It's very simple.

01:11:29.703 --> 01:11:31.454
You come over
to my house,

01:11:31.538 --> 01:11:33.290
and I'll forget
the whole thing.

01:11:33.373 --> 01:11:34.874
You are disgusting.

01:11:34.958 --> 01:11:36.418
Is that a no?

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:38.378
Too bad.

01:11:38.461 --> 01:11:39.963
Mr. Hart,
I'm begging you,

01:11:40.046 --> 01:11:41.881
think about
what you're doing.

01:11:41.965 --> 01:11:45.427
I didn't start this.
You three girls
did all the plotting.

01:11:45.510 --> 01:11:47.262
I won't let you
do this!

01:11:47.345 --> 01:11:49.723
There's another phone
over there, Doralee.

01:11:49.806 --> 01:11:51.391
Incidentally,
that's something else

01:11:51.474 --> 01:11:53.727
you might want
to think about.

01:11:53.810 --> 01:11:56.229
I'm very funny,
but I don't like it

01:11:56.313 --> 01:11:58.648
when people give back
my presents.

01:11:58.732 --> 01:12:00.608
Oh, you are rotten,
Mr. Hart.

01:12:00.692 --> 01:12:02.610
Did anybody
ever tell you that?

01:12:02.694 --> 01:12:06.114
I never thought
I'd say this about
another human being,

01:12:06.197 --> 01:12:08.825
but you are evil‒
evil to the core!

01:12:08.908 --> 01:12:11.328
I love it when you
get mad like that.

01:12:11.411 --> 01:12:15.457
If you touch that phone,
I'll jerk it
clean out of the wall.

01:12:15.540 --> 01:12:17.334
Ooh...

01:12:17.417 --> 01:12:19.294
I mean it!

01:12:19.377 --> 01:12:22.005
You think this
is all a joke.

01:12:22.088 --> 01:12:24.174
You're going to
listen to me

01:12:24.257 --> 01:12:26.009
whether you like it
or not!

01:12:26.092 --> 01:12:28.928
Will you shut up now
and let me explain
what happened?

01:12:29.012 --> 01:12:32.140
Let me loose
or I'm calling for help.

01:12:32.223 --> 01:12:35.268
No, I don't want you
to call for help.

01:12:35.352 --> 01:12:38.271
You won't listen,
but you'll shut up
and stay there!

01:12:38.355 --> 01:12:40.857
I got to figure out
what to do.

01:12:43.777 --> 01:12:44.694
Roz.

01:12:44.778 --> 01:12:46.196
Is Mr. Hart in?

01:12:46.279 --> 01:12:50.200
Yeah‒well, yeah,
but he's tied up
at the moment.

01:12:50.283 --> 01:12:51.201
Oh. Well...

01:12:51.284 --> 01:12:53.870
I guess it can wait
until Monday.

01:12:53.953 --> 01:12:55.372
Have a nice weekend.

01:12:55.455 --> 01:12:56.831
Yeah, you, too, Roz.

01:12:56.915 --> 01:12:57.874
Oh, Judy.

01:12:57.957 --> 01:13:00.335
Can you come here
a second?

01:13:00.418 --> 01:13:01.836
You ready, Doralee?

01:13:01.920 --> 01:13:04.839
No! Something awful
has happened.
Where's Violet?

01:13:04.923 --> 01:13:07.842
She's in
the storage room.
What's the matter?

01:13:07.926 --> 01:13:10.345
Hart knows everything
about last night.

01:13:10.428 --> 01:13:11.429
What?

01:13:11.513 --> 01:13:14.682
He really thinks
we were trying to kill him.

01:13:14.766 --> 01:13:17.185
He was going to
have us arrested.

01:13:17.268 --> 01:13:18.686
Oh, dear God.

01:13:18.770 --> 01:13:20.688
Get in there
and watch him.

01:13:20.772 --> 01:13:23.191
Lock that door,
and don't let
anybody in.

01:13:23.274 --> 01:13:24.526
I'm getting Violet.

01:13:24.609 --> 01:13:26.736
Oh, dear God.

01:13:27.821 --> 01:13:29.656
Oh, dear God.

01:13:34.828 --> 01:13:37.247
Mr. Hart, I'm so sorry.

01:13:38.998 --> 01:13:40.417
What?

01:13:40.500 --> 01:13:43.420
Oh, I can't understand
what you're saying.

01:13:46.631 --> 01:13:49.259
Thank God one of you
has come to your senses.

01:13:49.342 --> 01:13:50.677
Now get me loose.

01:13:50.760 --> 01:13:53.096
Doralee didn't mean
any harm, Mr. Hart.

01:13:53.179 --> 01:13:54.597
Just get me untied, okay?

01:13:54.681 --> 01:13:56.933
I can't do that
until they come back.

01:13:57.016 --> 01:13:59.394
You think
I'm going to run away?

01:13:59.477 --> 01:14:01.896
I won't do anything.
I give you
my word of honor.

01:14:01.980 --> 01:14:06.276
Just get me untied.
There's a little pain
involved here.

01:14:06.359 --> 01:14:07.777
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:14:07.861 --> 01:14:10.780
Maybe I'll just
loosen it a little bit.

01:14:10.864 --> 01:14:12.115
Good. Loosen it.

01:14:12.198 --> 01:14:15.076
You've got to understand
what happened last night.

01:14:15.160 --> 01:14:18.079
It was just a series
of misunderstandings.

01:14:18.163 --> 01:14:20.582
Violet didn't mean
to kill you.

01:14:20.665 --> 01:14:24.085
She just accidentally
put rat poison
in your coffee.

01:14:24.169 --> 01:14:26.087
Get out of my way!

01:14:26.171 --> 01:14:27.088
Mr. Hart.

01:14:27.172 --> 01:14:29.424
Mr. Hart,
you gave me your word!

01:14:29.507 --> 01:14:30.967
I lied.

01:14:31.050 --> 01:14:32.469
God damn it.

01:14:32.552 --> 01:14:34.429
You're not leaving
this office.

01:14:34.512 --> 01:14:35.972
Watch me.

01:14:36.055 --> 01:14:38.475
I was just pretending
a while ago,

01:14:38.558 --> 01:14:40.977
but this thing
is getting out of hand.

01:14:41.060 --> 01:14:43.605
Nobody makes a fool
out of me
in my own office.

01:14:43.688 --> 01:14:45.148
I'm calling the police.

01:14:46.524 --> 01:14:47.984
Hold it right there.

01:14:49.235 --> 01:14:51.488
You're as crazy
as the other two.

01:14:51.571 --> 01:14:54.699
Close that door
or I'll shoot.

01:14:57.577 --> 01:14:58.620
Aah!

01:14:58.703 --> 01:15:01.331
Hold it! Don't shoot!
I give up!

01:15:01.414 --> 01:15:03.333
Don't shoot it!

01:15:03.416 --> 01:15:05.168
Judy, put it‒

01:15:05.251 --> 01:15:06.836
Judy, what are you doing?

01:15:06.920 --> 01:15:09.964
Oh, my God.

01:15:10.048 --> 01:15:11.591
Christ.

01:15:11.674 --> 01:15:14.761
He‒He was going
to call the police.

01:15:27.690 --> 01:15:30.527
I just feel terrible
doing this to him.

01:15:30.610 --> 01:15:34.531
We'll get him to his place
and try to reason with him.

01:15:34.614 --> 01:15:37.283
His wife's on vacation,
and that house
is so far off the road,

01:15:37.367 --> 01:15:39.953
if he yells,
ain't nobody gonna hear him.

01:15:48.628 --> 01:15:50.380
So what do we do now?

01:15:50.463 --> 01:15:51.839
You'll pay for this.

01:15:51.923 --> 01:15:54.467
I swear you'll pay for this.

01:15:54.551 --> 01:15:55.885
If you'd only listen.

01:15:55.969 --> 01:15:57.178
You listen to me.

01:15:57.262 --> 01:16:00.431
I'll see you all in prison
before I'm through.

01:16:00.515 --> 01:16:01.432
Kidnapping.

01:16:01.516 --> 01:16:02.725
Attempted murder.

01:16:02.809 --> 01:16:04.185
Roped, beaten,

01:16:04.269 --> 01:16:05.728
rat poison.

01:16:05.812 --> 01:16:08.648
I won't rest
until you all get
20 years in prison!

01:16:08.731 --> 01:16:10.191
You understand that?

01:16:10.275 --> 01:16:11.276
20 years!

01:16:12.318 --> 01:16:13.903
God!

01:16:13.987 --> 01:16:16.823
We can't just
keep him here forever.

01:16:16.906 --> 01:16:18.324
Oh, you heard him.

01:16:18.408 --> 01:16:19.826
He don't believe us.

01:16:19.909 --> 01:16:21.327
He wants
to prosecute.

01:16:21.411 --> 01:16:22.954
Why wouldn't he?
He's got you
for poisoning him

01:16:23.037 --> 01:16:24.247
and me for roping him

01:16:24.330 --> 01:16:28.501
and you for acting like
he was first prize
in a turkey shoot.

01:16:28.585 --> 01:16:32.505
How are we going
to keep him from talking?

01:16:33.923 --> 01:16:35.425
I say we hire
a couple of wranglers

01:16:35.508 --> 01:16:37.677
to go upstairs
and beat the shit
out of him.

01:16:40.972 --> 01:16:44.183
If we could only
find something on him,
maybe we could trade off.

01:16:44.267 --> 01:16:45.935
Blackmail.
All that sounds good.

01:16:46.019 --> 01:16:48.021
What could we
get on him?

01:16:50.356 --> 01:16:51.774
A sex scandal.

01:16:51.858 --> 01:16:55.111
Take a picture of him
in bed with a prostitute.

01:16:55.194 --> 01:16:57.780
Oh, who would care?

01:16:57.864 --> 01:17:00.241
Hart would just
buy up the copies

01:17:00.325 --> 01:17:03.244
and send them out
as Christmas cards.

01:17:05.872 --> 01:17:07.206
Oh, Lord.

01:17:18.259 --> 01:17:19.677
We've gone over
everything.

01:17:19.761 --> 01:17:22.680
Well, we might
as well face it.

01:17:22.764 --> 01:17:25.224
He's got us.
We're licked.

01:17:25.308 --> 01:17:28.144
Wait a minute.
What's this doing here?

01:17:29.228 --> 01:17:30.730
What?

01:17:32.523 --> 01:17:35.985
Maybe we do have something
to bargain with after all.

01:17:36.069 --> 01:17:37.320
What is it?

01:17:37.403 --> 01:17:41.032
An account book
for Ajax Warehouse.

01:17:49.999 --> 01:17:52.919
There's
something suspicious
going on here.

01:17:53.002 --> 01:17:55.922
This is out
in the middle of nowhere.

01:17:57.090 --> 01:17:58.508
What do you see?

01:17:58.591 --> 01:18:00.009
Nothing.
It's too dark.

01:18:00.093 --> 01:18:03.054
Why don't you
climb up to that window?

01:18:18.403 --> 01:18:20.321
I think we got him.

01:18:20.405 --> 01:18:22.824
Ha, ha, ha!
I think we got him!

01:18:22.907 --> 01:18:23.991
Aah!

01:18:25.535 --> 01:18:26.953
Whoo! Yes, indeed,

01:18:27.036 --> 01:18:30.123
it looks like Frank
has been a very
naughty boy.

01:18:30.206 --> 01:18:32.291
An empty warehouse?

01:18:33.376 --> 01:18:35.044
What's wrong with that?

01:18:35.128 --> 01:18:37.547
That's what
Billie Sol Estes
said,

01:18:37.630 --> 01:18:40.049
and they gave him
15 years
for embezzlement.

01:18:40.133 --> 01:18:42.552
That warehouse
is supposed to be
filled with inventory

01:18:42.635 --> 01:18:44.137
from Consolidated.

01:18:44.220 --> 01:18:46.973
But you sold it
and pocketed the money.

01:18:47.056 --> 01:18:48.725
You can't prove that.

01:18:48.808 --> 01:18:51.185
I'm going to order
the invoices

01:18:51.269 --> 01:18:53.187
from head office,
on Monday.

01:18:53.271 --> 01:18:57.567
I think you'll...
see the light
when they arrive.

01:18:57.650 --> 01:18:59.527
You start tangling with me,

01:18:59.610 --> 01:19:02.530
you'd better be prepared
to play very rough,

01:19:02.613 --> 01:19:05.533
because I'm not
going to be stopped

01:19:05.616 --> 01:19:07.493
by three
dumb-witted broads.

01:19:07.577 --> 01:19:08.578
I'm not‒

01:19:11.497 --> 01:19:12.915
I'm going to get loose.

01:19:12.999 --> 01:19:14.917
I'm going to break loose

01:19:15.001 --> 01:19:18.421
if I have to kill somebody
to do it.

01:19:18.504 --> 01:19:21.424
To keep him tied up
three of four days,

01:19:21.507 --> 01:19:24.177
we need a better
system of confinement.

01:19:24.260 --> 01:19:26.596
Yes. Something that
limits his movement,

01:19:26.679 --> 01:19:30.349
but it should
wear well
and be comfortable.

01:19:52.538 --> 01:19:55.917
We figure you'll
sign our statement
by the end of the week,

01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:58.419
and then we'll
be able to let you go.

01:19:58.503 --> 01:20:00.922
I got all the razors
and the scissors

01:20:01.005 --> 01:20:02.924
and all the glass,
just in case.

